  "body": "My Geth client doesn't seem to start, printing \"Block state missing, rewinding further\" logs.\r\n\r\nI guess the main reason why is that the client accidentally shutted down because of out of storage space a couple of days ago. \r\n\r\nAfter that, I keep failing to get it back, every time I try to restart the node, though. :(\r\n\r\nOf course, I volume up the mounted disk.\r\n\r\nHere's my running commend.\r\n\r\n```console\r\n**Geth --cache=2048 --http --http.addr 0.0.0.0 --rpc.allow-unprotected-txs --datadir=/data/.ethereum --verbosity 5**\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf someone is here what happens, and how to make it work, please let me know what I should do.\r\n\r\nI also attached logs below.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1351\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2022-07-21 at 6 27 56 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/62552009/180188817-9909eabc-37e4-4f78-b6f0-7353009f4885.png\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"898\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2022-07-21 at 7 09 09 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/62552009/180189283-e5d022db-9995-4045-bdb6-581683aad28d.png\">\r\n\r\n",
